            . I am a constable. I was with Colton; I have heard what he said - I saw Kreele throw down the handkerchief, and I took Herswell; at the station, Krelle said that the other prisoner picked it up, and gave it to him.</p>
               <p>THOMAS GWYLLYM. This is my handkerchief; it has my name on it - I lost it in Finsbury-square; I cannot say that I saw the prisoners running - I saw some persons running; perhaps they were among them.</p>
               <p>The prisoners received a good character.</p>
